    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.22.9"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">9</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">LELAND D CASE
                        <lb/>
                    EDITOR
                        <lb/>
                    PAUL TEETOR
                        <lb/>
                    BUSINESS AND 
                        <lb/>
                    ADVERTISING MANAGER</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    
                    <hi rend="underline">The <hi rend="caps">ROTARIAN
                        <lb/>
                    OFFICIAL MAGAZINE OF ROTARY INTERNATIONAL</hi></hi>
                        <lb/>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">TELEPHONE 
                        <lb/>
                    STATE 4016
                        <lb/>
                    35 EAST WACKER DRIVE
                        <lb/>
                    CHICAGO 1, ILL.
                        <lb/>
                    U.S.A.</hi>
                </fw>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        June Seventeenth
                        1   9   4   8
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear John:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Just back from a long, long trip to our convention at Rio, returning via La Paz, Cuzco, and Lima, I discovered your welcome letter of May 17. Indeed, a long time has skidded by since we were in touch, so I am delighted to hear from you - and only wish that instead of the letter you, in person, were to come through the door.</p>
                
                <p>My congratulations to you on the long overdue job that Macmillans have finally undertaken. Many times I have thought that your <hi rend="underline">Cycle of the West</hi> should be collected in a volume for it is truly literature which merits a long life. As has none other, you have captured the epic spirit of the West.</p>
                
                <p>I hope the new book is coming along as rapidly as you desire. It sounds interesting and I'll be one of the first to purchase a copy, I assure you, and shall hope that you will personalize it for me as you have so many others.</p>
                
                <p>We miss you at our meetings!</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very cordially yours,</salute>
                    <signed>Leland
                    Editor</signed>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine><hi rend="caps">P. O.</hi> Box 305</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Branson, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <opener>
                        <hi rend="caps">P.S.</hi>
                    </opener>
                    <p><unclear>I've</unclear> just finished two chapters for a new book on the Black Hills &#8212; in the Mountains of America series.</p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
